1
00:00:19,167 --> 00:00:20,833
Why are you taking me
to places

2
00:00:20,900 --> 00:00:23,433
that are full of memories
of the two of us?

3
00:00:23,500 --> 00:00:26,000
I can't help but suspect...

4
00:00:26,067 --> 00:00:27,967
that you're not telling me
the truth.

5
00:00:28,033 --> 00:00:29,967
I don't know why are you
thinking that?

6
00:00:30,033 --> 00:00:31,533
Do you still love me?

7
00:00:31,600 --> 00:00:32,933
Yes or no.

8
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:34,367
Do you still love me, Mikoy?

9
00:00:38,833 --> 00:00:40,500
No.

10
00:00:40,567 --> 00:00:42,067
I don't love you anymore.

11
00:00:42,133 --> 00:00:45,967
You can calm down because
everything I do have no malice.

12
00:00:46,033 --> 00:00:46,967
Why did you push through
with it?

13
00:00:47,033 --> 00:00:48,167
You got humiliated.

14
00:00:48,233 --> 00:00:50,600
Celeste is also family now.

15
00:00:50,667 --> 00:00:53,167
Not unless I accept her
as your wife.

16
00:00:53,233 --> 00:00:55,833
I keep on seeking for approval
from others.

17
00:00:55,900 --> 00:00:58,900
Because the only approval
I'm seeking right now...

18
00:00:58,967 --> 00:01:00,333
is from me.

19
00:01:00,400 --> 00:01:03,500
You know very well that
my father and I are not okay.

20
00:01:03,567 --> 00:01:05,033
And you will take me here?

21
00:01:05,100 --> 00:01:07,533
I brought you here because
Sorsogon is the number one

22
00:01:07,633 --> 00:01:09,567
producer of Pili in the country.

23
00:01:09,633 --> 00:01:11,067
And we need to promote that.

24
00:01:11,133 --> 00:01:12,267
Really now?

25
00:01:12,333 --> 00:01:13,833
Not everything is about you.

26
00:01:13,900 --> 00:01:16,100
No matter how good you are
as a businessman,

27
00:01:16,167 --> 00:01:17,367
nothing will prepare you

28
00:01:17,433 --> 00:01:20,333
for the most difficult
business deal in your life...

29
00:01:20,400 --> 00:01:21,833
your daughter.

30
00:01:21,900 --> 00:01:24,200
I hope she can accept
my decision and Celeste's.

31
00:01:24,267 --> 00:01:25,200
Celeste, look.

32
00:01:25,267 --> 00:01:26,967
I'm sorry.

33
00:01:27,033 --> 00:01:29,633
I didn't know you're that angry
with your father.

34
00:01:29,700 --> 00:01:31,400
Well, I appreciate your concern.

35
00:01:31,467 --> 00:01:34,667
Please next time don't meddle.

36
00:01:34,733 --> 00:01:35,700
You're just messing things up.

37
00:02:09,500 --> 00:02:10,867
Wait a second.

38
00:02:23,867 --> 00:02:25,633
Celeste, you're tired, right?

39
00:02:27,633 --> 00:02:28,667
You have no idea.

40
00:02:30,733 --> 00:02:33,167
You should rest.

41
00:02:33,233 --> 00:02:37,167
It's hard to get your hands
tired, you might injure it.

42
00:02:37,233 --> 00:02:39,733
You're using them
when you draw.

43
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:42,200
Your mother Lucinda
will get mad at me.

44
00:02:44,233 --> 00:02:46,100
Celeste...

45
00:02:46,167 --> 00:02:48,700
your mother's
death anniversary is near.

46
00:02:49,933 --> 00:02:50,900
Do you have plans already?

47
00:02:54,633 --> 00:02:55,667
Nothing.

48
00:03:01,700 --> 00:03:04,333
This is the first time
you returned to this place

49
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:06,933
since your mother died.

50
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:08,467
When she left us...

51
00:03:10,500 --> 00:03:12,500
this place
also died at the same time.

52
00:03:13,533 --> 00:03:15,767
I said back then...

53
00:03:15,833 --> 00:03:17,267
that it seems...

54
00:03:17,333 --> 00:03:20,267
Lucinda brought the seedlings
with her in the afterlife.

55
00:03:21,467 --> 00:03:25,933
I planned to sell this but
I couldn't bring myself to do it

56
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:30,767
because I said your mother and I

57
00:03:30,833 --> 00:03:33,000
had a lot of good memories
in this place.

58
00:03:33,067 --> 00:03:37,367
I worked hard back then
to rebuild this place again.

59
00:03:40,100 --> 00:03:43,033
And I promised myself...

60
00:03:43,100 --> 00:03:45,833
that I won't let the seedlings
die again.

61
00:03:47,700 --> 00:03:49,400
So I can make it up to
your mother...

62
00:03:51,333 --> 00:03:53,667
because I wasn't able
to take care of her...

63
00:03:53,733 --> 00:03:55,067
while she was still alive.

64
00:03:56,133 --> 00:03:57,967
I can at least take care...

65
00:03:59,100 --> 00:04:00,567
of this one place...

66
00:04:02,100 --> 00:04:04,033
that reminds me of her.

67
00:04:05,233 --> 00:04:09,000
With the grace of God, I was
able to rebuild this place.

68
00:04:11,033 --> 00:04:11,900
I hope Celeste...

69
00:04:13,200 --> 00:04:18,400
you also won't neglect this farm

70
00:04:18,467 --> 00:04:23,200
because I don't want to lose...

71
00:04:23,267 --> 00:04:26,067
the remaining memory
of your mother to us.

72
00:04:36,300 --> 00:04:37,267
Stop crying, Celeste.

73
00:04:40,767 --> 00:04:42,633
Don't cry.

74
00:04:42,700 --> 00:04:43,700
Stop crying.

75
00:06:00,600 --> 00:06:02,500
I already read the contract.

76
00:06:02,567 --> 00:06:03,500
It looks like you won't be
at the losing end

77
00:06:03,567 --> 00:06:05,367
in in this deal
that you will get into.

78
00:06:05,433 --> 00:06:07,333
Thank you, Winston.
Just leave it there.

79
00:06:09,833 --> 00:06:11,000
What are you watching?

80
00:06:18,067 --> 00:06:20,367
Ah...

81
00:06:20,433 --> 00:06:23,667
that's why
you can't be disturbed.

82
00:06:23,733 --> 00:06:26,667
I bet half of its views
came from you.

83
00:06:28,500 --> 00:06:29,600
Not really.

84
00:06:32,767 --> 00:06:34,700
I won't be surprised.

85
00:06:34,767 --> 00:06:37,700
If I were Celeste,
I will get scared.

86
00:06:37,767 --> 00:06:39,900
You're not just in love,
you're obsessed.

87
00:06:42,400 --> 00:06:44,800
But seriously...

88
00:06:46,033 --> 00:06:48,967
I know that Celeste
is quite a wife material.

89
00:06:49,033 --> 00:06:51,867
But I wonder if she is
also a mother material.

90
00:06:53,500 --> 00:06:55,667
Can she be a mother to Tiffany?

91
00:06:55,733 --> 00:06:58,000
It's hard to raise your child.

92
00:06:58,067 --> 00:07:00,300
How much more
is she is not your own?

93
00:07:00,367 --> 00:07:03,767
You know when Aurelia
and I separated,

94
00:07:03,833 --> 00:07:06,000
I promised myself that
I will not marry again.

95
00:07:07,467 --> 00:07:10,267
That I will shower all
my time on Tiffany.

96
00:07:10,333 --> 00:07:12,267
Then I met Celeste.

97
00:07:14,867 --> 00:07:18,000
I didn't jump into
the relationship right away

98
00:07:18,067 --> 00:07:19,533
because I know that Tiffany
will have a hard time

99
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:20,700
accepting her...

100
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:23,367
and me too...

101
00:07:24,900 --> 00:07:28,000
because I was looking for more
than a stepmother for Tiffany.

102
00:07:29,033 --> 00:07:30,733
I was looking
for a second mother.

103
00:07:33,133 --> 00:07:34,667
But what's good about Celeste...

104
00:07:35,933 --> 00:07:38,500
is that she knows how to love
someone without being pushy.

105
00:07:39,867 --> 00:07:41,633
She's not overwhelming.

106
00:07:41,700 --> 00:07:42,933
She knows where she stands.

107
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:47,167
And she just doesn't do it
just for the praises.

108
00:07:48,433 --> 00:07:50,533
She's not doing this
just to impress me.

109
00:07:51,733 --> 00:07:55,033
She's doing it because
she's so selfless.

110
00:07:55,100 --> 00:07:58,533
And she knows how to love others
selflessly.

111
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:02,000
That's why I know that Celeste
is going to be

112
00:08:02,067 --> 00:08:04,067
a good second mother to Tiffany.

113
00:08:22,833 --> 00:08:26,100
I feel sorry for Sir Patricio.

114
00:08:26,700 --> 00:08:29,800
I saw that he's trying his best
to patch things up with Celeste.

115
00:08:33,800 --> 00:08:36,800
If he is really concerned
about her daughter,

116
00:08:36,867 --> 00:08:38,033
he will not give up on her.

117
00:08:41,267 --> 00:08:43,133
Can they still patch things up?

118
00:08:44,800 --> 00:08:48,233
This is the first time I saw
how angry Celeste is with him.

119
00:08:48,300 --> 00:08:49,800
It only means one thing.

120
00:08:51,467 --> 00:08:53,833
She loves her father deeply.

121
00:08:53,900 --> 00:08:58,167
The deeper the love,
the deeper the anger.

122
00:08:58,267 --> 00:09:06,600
Sometimes that anger will blind
you until your heart gets numb

123
00:09:06,667 --> 00:09:10,500
and you forget
for what it was created.

124
00:09:11,733 --> 00:09:18,433
But as time passes by,
it heals everything.

125
00:09:18,500 --> 00:09:22,033
That anger will be left
in the past until the heart

126
00:09:22,100 --> 00:09:26,567
remembers what it had
forgotten for a long time.

127
00:09:26,633 --> 00:09:28,033
That is to love again.

128
00:09:54,100 --> 00:09:58,367
Earlier Mother, father is trying
to make small talk with me.

129
00:10:00,133 --> 00:10:02,433
I can see that he's making
an effort but...

130
00:10:04,233 --> 00:10:06,800
I don't know,
I'm still so mad at him.

131
00:10:12,100 --> 00:10:14,300
I know that you want us
to reconcile...

132
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:18,867
because it's been a long time.

133
00:10:21,567 --> 00:10:23,300
How do I possibly forgive...

134
00:10:24,700 --> 00:10:26,767
the man that I love first?

135
00:10:29,267 --> 00:10:30,933
And was also the first one
to hurt me.

136
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:15,867
Celeste, you want?

137
00:11:15,933 --> 00:11:18,367
It came from our farm yesterday.

138
00:11:18,433 --> 00:11:20,700
I'm okay, thank you.

139
00:11:20,767 --> 00:11:21,767
Where is father?

140
00:11:23,033 --> 00:11:24,333
He left early.

141
00:11:24,400 --> 00:11:25,933
He will go somewhere important.

142
00:11:27,600 --> 00:11:28,733
Somewhere important?

143
00:11:29,833 --> 00:11:32,300
Yes but I wasn't able
to ask what it is.

144
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:37,967
Okay, well then,
I'll go ahead.

145
00:11:38,033 --> 00:11:39,167
You take care.

146
00:11:39,233 --> 00:11:41,000
Bye, take care.

147
00:11:43,600 --> 00:11:45,300
Good mood.

148
00:11:45,367 --> 00:11:46,467
She woke up on the right side
of the bed.

149
00:11:49,333 --> 00:11:52,833
See, he still remembers
your mom's death anniversary.

150
00:11:52,900 --> 00:11:57,467
Maybe he went ahead of you
in the cemetery.

151
00:11:57,533 --> 00:11:58,500
Do you think so?

152
00:11:59,900 --> 00:12:04,133
Didn't Sebastian say that he was
going somewhere important?

153
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:06,433
Who else he will go to?

154
00:12:06,500 --> 00:12:10,400
Well, I talked to him
one time about mother.

155
00:12:10,467 --> 00:12:12,600
I was a bit teary-eyed.

156
00:12:12,667 --> 00:12:15,800
Maybe we can patch
things up soon.

157
00:12:15,900 --> 00:12:18,867
Well, I think
that day is today.

158
00:12:21,333 --> 00:12:22,433
I hope so.

159
00:12:52,700 --> 00:12:55,967
What are we doing here?

160
00:12:56,033 --> 00:12:59,367
Let's just say that I picked
this place for our project.

161
00:12:59,433 --> 00:13:01,100
Wow!

162
00:13:01,167 --> 00:13:02,300
What's in here?

163
00:13:02,367 --> 00:13:04,600
It seems like there's nothing.

164
00:13:04,667 --> 00:13:06,233
What do you mean nothing?

165
00:13:06,300 --> 00:13:08,833
There's nothing
like this in Manila.

166
00:13:08,900 --> 00:13:10,367
And then I asked someone
for advice

167
00:13:10,433 --> 00:13:12,833
and this is what he suggested.

168
00:13:12,900 --> 00:13:14,333
Who is that?

169
00:13:14,400 --> 00:13:15,800
It's me.

170
00:13:15,867 --> 00:13:16,967
Hi, Basti!

171
00:13:17,033 --> 00:13:19,467
Hi!

172
00:13:19,533 --> 00:13:21,400
Did you ask for advice from him?

173
00:13:21,500 --> 00:13:22,667
Well, yes.

174
00:13:22,733 --> 00:13:28,967
Who else knows this place
but a legitimate Sorsoganon.

175
00:13:29,033 --> 00:13:30,167
It's okay if it's beautiful...

176
00:13:31,200 --> 00:13:33,300
but it's not.

177
00:13:33,367 --> 00:13:35,167
Now I know why.

178
00:13:35,233 --> 00:13:36,233
James...

179
00:13:39,533 --> 00:13:40,800
are you going
to pick a fight again?

180
00:13:53,833 --> 00:13:55,933
This beach is the next big
tourist destination

181
00:13:56,033 --> 00:13:57,333
in this place.

182
00:13:57,400 --> 00:13:59,433
You can choose
a location here.

183
00:13:59,500 --> 00:14:01,167
And soon they will open
this to the public

184
00:14:01,233 --> 00:14:03,367
under the management
of Sorsogon Tourism.

185
00:14:03,433 --> 00:14:06,633
And since it's new we expect
a lot of tourists.

186
00:14:06,700 --> 00:14:08,933
My gosh, that's so nice.

187
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:10,800
You know that's what really
people want.

188
00:14:10,867 --> 00:14:12,600
They always look
for new places.

189
00:14:12,667 --> 00:14:14,367
Let's find another one.

190
00:14:14,433 --> 00:14:15,600
I don't like this place.

191
00:14:17,633 --> 00:14:19,033
James, we can't.

192
00:14:19,100 --> 00:14:21,933
We're so late already.

193
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:23,867
Let's go to Botoan.

194
00:14:23,933 --> 00:14:25,700
I don't like this
provincial guy's recommendation.

195
00:14:27,300 --> 00:14:28,267
How about you?

196
00:14:30,333 --> 00:14:32,600
I love it. It's beautiful.

197
00:14:32,667 --> 00:14:33,800
Hey, let's take a picture.

198
00:14:37,700 --> 00:14:38,733
It's settled then.

199
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:41,833
Let's go.

200
00:15:08,700 --> 00:15:09,733
Hi, Mother.

201
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:17,767
Father, I'm already here.

202
00:15:24,667 --> 00:15:26,967
Father is still not here.

203
00:15:27,033 --> 00:15:28,200
Don't worry he's probably
on his way.

204
00:15:44,267 --> 00:15:45,567
I'm sorry the subscriber
could not be reached.

205
00:15:45,633 --> 00:15:47,100
I can't contact him, Mother.

206
00:15:50,133 --> 00:15:52,533
When was the last time
father visited you?

207
00:15:56,067 --> 00:15:58,400
Don't worry
maybe he's almost here.

208
00:16:03,133 --> 00:16:04,833
You will put up
a business here?

209
00:16:05,967 --> 00:16:07,867
That's not possible.

210
00:16:07,933 --> 00:16:09,967
The locals will not agree.

211
00:16:10,067 --> 00:16:13,600
Sir Ben, this is
for our school project.

212
00:16:13,667 --> 00:16:18,167
And Basti told us that we need
to ask for your permission.

213
00:16:18,233 --> 00:16:21,167
And besides this is a big help
for the locals here, Sir Ben.

214
00:16:21,233 --> 00:16:23,267
You will all have a livelihood.

215
00:16:23,333 --> 00:16:26,067
The thing is we avoid outsiders.

216
00:16:26,133 --> 00:16:29,467
Our place will be ruined.

217
00:16:29,533 --> 00:16:33,267
The only ones who can put up
a business here are the locals.

218
00:16:33,333 --> 00:16:36,267
Actually, Sir Ben...

219
00:16:36,333 --> 00:16:38,767
I'm not an outsider.

220
00:16:38,833 --> 00:16:40,200
I'm really from here.

221
00:16:43,767 --> 00:16:45,000
Basti is my boyfriend.

222
00:16:47,467 --> 00:16:48,933
Right, Babe?

223
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:50,000
Yes, Sir.

224
00:16:55,767 --> 00:17:00,200
And with that Sir Ben,
can we start the ocular?

225
00:17:00,267 --> 00:17:01,867
Okay.

226
00:17:01,933 --> 00:17:03,033
- Let's go.
- Explain to me

227
00:17:03,100 --> 00:17:04,767
what you will build.

228
00:17:04,833 --> 00:17:06,100
Come on.

229
00:17:06,167 --> 00:17:07,400
You should see this.

230
00:17:07,467 --> 00:17:12,300
Basti, I didn't expect
that you can have a girlfriend.

231
00:17:12,367 --> 00:17:13,300
Did your father allow you
to have a girlfriend?

232
00:17:13,367 --> 00:17:14,933
Yes.

233
00:17:15,033 --> 00:17:16,433
Did your father allow you
to have a girlfriend?

234
00:17:16,500 --> 00:17:17,700
Yes.

235
00:17:17,767 --> 00:17:18,800
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

236
00:17:18,867 --> 00:17:20,900
- You only eat ice cream before.
- No, Sir.

237
00:17:25,267 --> 00:17:28,767
Basti, I didn't know that
you are building a business.

238
00:17:28,833 --> 00:17:30,967
What do you plan to do?

239
00:17:31,033 --> 00:17:33,267
We plan to build a kiosk.

240
00:17:33,333 --> 00:17:34,767
- Kiosk?
- Yes.

241
00:17:34,833 --> 00:17:36,000
Okay.

242
00:17:36,067 --> 00:17:38,900
Who are your incorporators?

243
00:17:40,300 --> 00:17:42,033
Who are they, Clau?

244
00:17:42,100 --> 00:17:44,467
What will you sell?
There's a lot of...

245
00:17:44,533 --> 00:17:48,833
We just need two people...

246
00:17:48,933 --> 00:17:52,267
- Okay.
- to watch over the business.

247
00:17:52,333 --> 00:17:58,700
We can sell newspapers
and then refreshments.

248
00:17:58,767 --> 00:18:01,300
- That's perfect here.
- We can sell mango juice,

249
00:18:01,367 --> 00:18:04,167
fresh mango juice.

250
00:18:04,233 --> 00:18:07,733
Coconut and we can also
make shakes.

251
00:18:07,800 --> 00:18:09,200
We have a lot of coconuts here.

252
00:18:09,267 --> 00:18:12,267
- I'm sure they will buy that.
- Yes, right.

253
00:18:12,333 --> 00:18:13,800
Right, Babe?

254
00:18:13,867 --> 00:18:14,900
That's right.

255
00:18:18,967 --> 00:18:22,333
Have you already thought
of a name for your business?

256
00:18:22,433 --> 00:18:23,733
None yet.

257
00:18:23,800 --> 00:18:25,100
You should think about it

258
00:18:25,167 --> 00:18:29,267
especially
if it's a Sorsoganon word.

259
00:18:29,333 --> 00:18:31,733
- What could that be?
- A lot of people drink

260
00:18:31,800 --> 00:18:33,367
- and visit the beach
- Yes.

261
00:18:33,433 --> 00:18:35,300
especially if it's summer,
right?

262
00:18:39,733 --> 00:18:41,133
What's taking father so long.

263
00:18:44,467 --> 00:18:45,633
You know Mother...

264
00:18:47,400 --> 00:18:48,467
you will be glad.

265
00:18:50,733 --> 00:18:53,900
I've decided to patch things up
with father.

266
00:18:55,467 --> 00:18:57,200
You are the witness.

267
00:19:04,633 --> 00:19:05,600
Just let me know

268
00:19:05,667 --> 00:19:08,633
once you've made a decision,
Sebastian.

269
00:19:08,700 --> 00:19:10,367
Yes, Sir Ben.

270
00:19:10,433 --> 00:19:13,033
Thank you again
for accompanying us, Sir Ben.

271
00:19:13,100 --> 00:19:14,733
No problem.

272
00:19:14,800 --> 00:19:17,100
Okay, you take care.

273
00:19:17,167 --> 00:19:18,233
- Bye.
- Take care.

274
00:19:24,867 --> 00:19:27,200
Thank you so much, Basti.

275
00:19:27,267 --> 00:19:28,600
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

276
00:19:31,567 --> 00:19:33,933
Why do you have to pretend
like you're together?

277
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:35,600
Are you a couple now?

278
00:19:35,667 --> 00:19:36,633
Don't you get it?

279
00:19:38,200 --> 00:19:40,967
They don't take outsiders here.

280
00:19:41,033 --> 00:19:42,900
I know what you're saying
is just an excuse

281
00:19:42,967 --> 00:19:44,800
so you can flirt with him.

282
00:19:47,933 --> 00:19:50,100
And you,
you're are an opportunist.

283
00:19:50,167 --> 00:19:51,100
- James?
- Am I the one

284
00:19:51,167 --> 00:19:52,133
who thought of that?

285
00:19:52,200 --> 00:19:54,067
It was your girlfriend's idea.

286
00:19:54,133 --> 00:19:57,700
I bet you can't get a woman
by yourself, can you?

287
00:19:57,767 --> 00:19:58,800
James, stop!

288
00:19:58,867 --> 00:20:03,933
Well, who will fall
for a loser like you?

289
00:20:04,033 --> 00:20:05,900
James. James, what's with you?

290
00:20:05,967 --> 00:20:07,033
Basti, please go home.

291
00:20:07,100 --> 00:20:09,067
Let's go, James.
What's with you?

292
00:20:09,133 --> 00:20:11,600
I will not leave
with that fool!

293
00:20:11,667 --> 00:20:13,333
What did you say?

294
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:14,967
James, what's with you?

295
00:20:15,033 --> 00:20:16,467
James, what's with you?

296
00:20:16,533 --> 00:20:17,567
What's with you?

297
00:20:17,633 --> 00:20:19,700
Basti, please...

298
00:20:21,800 --> 00:20:22,767
go home.

299
00:20:39,967 --> 00:20:41,433
What the heck is your problem?

300
00:20:42,900 --> 00:20:44,200
He helped us.

301
00:20:44,267 --> 00:20:45,433
Sir Ben might hear us.

302
00:20:45,500 --> 00:20:46,867
Am I the one who has a problem?
Did I do something wrong?

303
00:20:46,933 --> 00:20:47,900
Yes...

304
00:20:49,767 --> 00:20:51,867
because you are narrow-minded.

305
00:20:51,933 --> 00:20:53,667
You flirted right
in front of my face!

306
00:20:53,733 --> 00:20:59,767
It was just a freaking
scheme, James.

307
00:20:59,833 --> 00:21:02,067
Do you think we can enter
this beach if Basti and I

308
00:21:02,133 --> 00:21:04,267
didn't pretend that
we're a couple?

309
00:21:04,333 --> 00:21:08,367
If you still can't understand,
you're on your own.

310
00:21:12,500 --> 00:21:13,667
Tiff, wait!

311
00:21:21,633 --> 00:21:24,100
You should've fetched Celeste.

312
00:21:26,233 --> 00:21:28,633
Grandma, she asked for a leave.

313
00:21:28,700 --> 00:21:31,300
It's the death anniversary
of her mother Lucinda.

314
00:21:31,367 --> 00:21:33,433
Why didn't you go with her?

315
00:21:33,500 --> 00:21:39,233
That is your chance to show
that you comfort her.

316
00:21:39,300 --> 00:21:40,400
Grandma, that's not my job.

317
00:21:40,467 --> 00:21:41,833
That's the job of her fiancé.

318
00:21:41,900 --> 00:21:43,000
He's not here.

319
00:21:44,533 --> 00:21:45,700
You are tolerating that.

320
00:21:45,767 --> 00:21:46,967
That's the truth.

321
00:21:48,867 --> 00:21:50,033
I'm just kidding.

322
00:21:50,100 --> 00:21:51,200
What's with you?

323
00:21:51,267 --> 00:21:52,700
But Mikoy...

324
00:21:52,767 --> 00:21:57,600
my point is just to remember
what I said to you earlier.

325
00:21:57,667 --> 00:22:01,367
There's nothing that
time can't heal.

326
00:22:01,433 --> 00:22:04,400
You should leave the anger
in the past.

327
00:22:04,467 --> 00:22:09,800
Until the heart remembers
what it had long forgotten.

328
00:22:09,867 --> 00:22:11,533
That is to love again?

329
00:22:18,100 --> 00:22:19,400
Where will I put this?

330
00:22:19,467 --> 00:22:20,433
Over there.

331
00:22:24,200 --> 00:22:25,400
Am I the one
who should carry that?

332
00:22:25,467 --> 00:22:26,467
You should carry that.

333
00:22:26,533 --> 00:22:27,467
Okay, I'll do it.

334
00:22:27,533 --> 00:22:30,100
You're so big and I'm so small.

335
00:22:30,167 --> 00:22:31,800
This kid is really something.

336
00:22:32,867 --> 00:22:34,633
How are you?

337
00:22:34,700 --> 00:22:35,800
Are you okay?

338
00:22:54,500 --> 00:22:55,567
Not really.

339
00:23:00,567 --> 00:23:02,300
Don't worry, I'll bring
you pili the next time

340
00:23:02,367 --> 00:23:04,867
we see each other.

341
00:23:09,033 --> 00:23:12,233
Don't worry, I'll bring
you pili the next time

342
00:23:12,300 --> 00:23:13,300
we see each other.

343
00:23:18,333 --> 00:23:21,100
You made me smile a bit there.

344
00:23:21,167 --> 00:23:22,667
Thanks for making me smile.

345
00:23:25,133 --> 00:23:35,100
No problem, Pili Girl.
See you again.

346
00:23:56,867 --> 00:23:57,867
Nothing.

347
00:24:01,400 --> 00:24:03,667
Maybe he has no plans
of coming, Mother.

348
00:24:05,100 --> 00:24:06,300
I can't contact him.

349
00:24:09,667 --> 00:24:11,367
It's my fault.
I expected too much.

350
00:24:14,667 --> 00:24:15,667
Anyway...

351
00:24:21,367 --> 00:24:23,233
I'll come back, Mother.

352
00:25:05,667 --> 00:25:06,567
Yes, Vivian.

353
00:25:06,633 --> 00:25:09,467
I'll send you
some documents tonight.

354
00:25:09,533 --> 00:25:11,567
Vivian will send some documents.

355
00:25:11,633 --> 00:25:16,600
Do you know what it is?

356
00:25:16,667 --> 00:25:24,667
James?

357
00:25:24,733 --> 00:25:27,000
Tiffany is having a hard time.

358
00:25:27,067 --> 00:25:29,000
I'm getting married
in four months.

359
00:25:29,067 --> 00:25:30,767
She has to accept that.

360
00:25:30,833 --> 00:25:32,767
You and Celeste are really over?

361
00:25:32,833 --> 00:25:34,100
Even if lightning strikes you?

362
00:25:35,567 --> 00:25:36,800
Ah...

363
00:25:36,867 --> 00:25:40,967
See, you can't say it because
lightning might strike you.

364
00:25:41,033 --> 00:25:43,233
Mikoy, we need your help.

365
00:25:43,300 --> 00:25:44,633
Celeste is missing.

366
00:25:44,700 --> 00:25:46,433
Let's look for her.

367
00:25:46,500 --> 00:25:48,133
I think you're good to go.

368
00:25:48,200 --> 00:25:48,900
It's already late.

369
00:25:53,000 --> 00:25:56,467
Ouch, you're heavy.

370
00:25:56,533 --> 00:25:57,667
What are you doing?

371
00:25:57,733 --> 00:26:00,267
Wait.

372
00:26:00,333 --> 00:26:02,667
Just relax.

373
00:26:02,733 --> 00:26:03,967
That's vulgar.

374
00:26:04,033 --> 00:26:04,967
Do you want me
to stop getting dressed?

375
00:26:07,767 --> 00:26:09,967
Do you remember the day
I carved this?

376
00:26:10,067 --> 00:26:13,933
That's also the day
when we kissed.

377
00:26:14,000 --> 00:26:15,767
What? Are you hallucinating?

378
00:26:15,833 --> 00:26:18,133
No kiss took place.

379
00:26:18,200 --> 00:26:20,500
On the cheek.

380
00:26:20,567 --> 00:26:22,000
Lips.

381
00:26:22,067 --> 00:26:23,033
Hey.
